Testing #62073

I made the `getChildren` wait 2 seconds before returning:

```ts
		getChildren: (element: { key: string }): Thenable<{ key: string }[]> => {
			return new Promise(resolve => {
				setTimeout(() => {
					resolve(getChildren(element ? element.key : undefined).map(key => getNode(key)))
				}, 2000)
			})
		},
```

The result of using `Reveal` on `aaaaa`: Nothing happens for 10 seconds.

I think we should use the progress API for indication.

Allow the ability to reference an existing token

### Use case

Instead of needing to have

```json
  "editor.tokenColorCustomizations": {
    "[Default Dark+]": {
      "textMateRules": [
        {
          "scope": "markup.italic",
          "settings": {
            "foreground": "#dcdcaa"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    "[Default Light+]": {
      "textMateRules": [
        {
          "scope": "markup.italic",
          "settings": {
            "foreground": "#795e26"
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  }
```

in which the foreground color is copied from the `support.function` foreground color of each theme and repeating for each theme, something similar to the following:

```json
  "editor.tokenColorCustomizations": {
    "textMateRules": [
      {
        "scope": "markup.italic",
        "settings": {
          "foreground": {
            "referenceScope": "support.function",
            "referenceSetting": "foreground"
          }
        }
      }
    ]
  }
```
